==Untitled== There is no evidence of presence of electronic surveilence aboard the Catalinas.
The Catalinas were on international waters.
: Both of the above statements are correct. The shot-down ''Catalina'' ('''not plural''') was not on a surveilence mission, but on a rescue mission, searching for the lost DC-3 aircraft. [[User:83.250.228.140|83.250.228.140]] 20:50, 5 August 2006 (UTC)
== clarification ==
so how many of the supposed (8) original ypb crew ditched, died, were rescued? :All five crew members from the Canso were rescued by the German freighter.[[User:83.248.24.253|83.248.24.253]] 14:35, 28 October 2006 (UTC)
